content:
Use custom queries to apply user-defined values to dimensions, measures, and limits of other queries. For example, you can create a toggle widget that filters case records based on the following user-defined values: High Priority Cases, Medium Priority Cases, and Low Priority Cases.

To enable these custom values to filter your data, you map them to your data using a binding.

To open the queries panel, click an empty space in the dashboard canvas. Click Create Query. Click Create Custom Query. Click +Add Column to add a dimension, measure, text, or number as a column to your custom query.

For a dimension or measure, choose a dataset. Click +Add to add rows to your custom query. For a measure, choose a function. For a dimension or measure, choose a field.

To make changes, find the query in the query panel, click , then Edit. You can change the query name, add and remove columns, add row and column values, reorder columns, and pick values from a dataset.

Drag the list or toggle widget from the widget toolbar to the dashboard canvas. Drag the custom query on top of the widget. The widget shows the custom display values as selection options.

To customize the appearance of the widget, set the widget properties. Bind the values of the custom query to other widgets to specify how a selection in this query affects other widgets.
title: Custom Queries in Salesforce CRM Analytics
